{
  "texts": [
    "Developing a fully updatable learned multidimensional index will require data layout designs and efficient model update strategies.",
    "Additionally, a wellcrafted cost model should be established to seamlessly embed learned indexes into DBMS with cost-based optimizers.",
    "IO-Efficient and Cache-Efficient Learned Index.",
    "Existing works on learned indexes mainly target on inmemory query processing.",
    "Although LISA [47] and RSMI [69] claim that they can be adapted for disk-based storage, they do not specifically optimize for disk access characteristics."
  ]
}